'''Bachelor of Computer Applications''' ('''BCA''') is a four-year undergraduate degree in Nepal and three-year undergraduate degree course in India. This is the field of computer applications/computer science. After BCA the students can do further studies as MCA master in computer application.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://beta.nielit.gov.in/kohima/content/syllabus-bachelor-computer-application-bca|title=Syllabus for Bachelor of Computer Application|last=|first=|date=|website=National Institute of Electronics & Information Technology,Kohima|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.msuniv.ac.in/|title=Manonmaniam Sundaranar University|last=|first=|date=|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.suniv.ac.in/ |title=Sambalpur University |last=|first=|date=|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ggu.ac.in |title=Guru Ghasidas University |last=|first=|date=|publisher=}}</ref> It is a common degree for CS/IT in Indian universities and is an alternative to the engineering counterpart, BE/BTech in Computer Science and Engineering/IT which takes 4 years. It is a technical degree that prepares students for a career in the field of computer applications and [[software development]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://targetstudy.com/courses/bca.html |title=B.C.A., Bachelor of Computer Applications, Syllabus, Eligibility, Duration, Degree Course |publisher=Targetstudy.com |date=2018-03-27 |accessdate=2018-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cbsmohali.org/bca.html |title=Bachelors in Computer Applications (BCA) |publisher=Cbsmohali.org |date= |accessdate=2018-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uni-mysore.ac.in/ |title=UNIVERSITY OF MYSORE &#124; ಮೈಸೂರು ವಿಶ್ವವಿದ್ಯಾನಿಲಯ |publisher=Uni-mysore.ac.in |date= |accessdate=2018-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universityofcalicut.info/ |title=Official website of Calicut University - Home |publisher=Universityofcalicut.info |date= |accessdate=2018-04-22}}</ref><r